      "description": [
        "{{sbc|Crystal Spires:}} '''Skarner's''' presence causes a number of ''Crystal Spires'' to appear at set points on the battlefield, which can be captured by {{tip|champions}} who stand near them for 2 seconds. Once captured, ''Crystal Spires'' are owned until contested and the defending team can stand on the spire to prevent the opposing team from capturing it.",
        "''Crystal Spires'' grant {{g|30}} split among its captors upon being captured, or {{g|15}} if only a single champion participated in its capture, and provide {{tip|sight}} around them for {{fd|1.5}} seconds upon being captured, becoming impossible to recapture for 15 seconds.",
        "{{sbc|Crystal Charge:}} While within range of a ''Crystal Spire'' controlled by his team, or while an enemy is {{tip|stun|stunned}} with {{ai|Fracture|Skarner}} or {{tip|suppression|suppressed}} with {{ai|Impale|Skarner}}, '''Skarner''' gains {{pp|18|70|72|74|76|78|80|82|85|88|91|94|97|100|104|108|112|116|120|formula = 68 + 2 per level up to 7, + 3 per level up to 13, and + 4 per level|color=ms}} {{sti|ms|{{as|'''bonus''' movement speed}}}}, {{pp|18|key=%|43|48|53|58|63|68|73|80|87|94|101|108|115|124|133|142|151|160|formula = 38 + 5 per level up to 7, + 7 per level up to 13, and + 9 per level|color=as}} {{sti|{{as|'''bonus''' attack speed}}}} and restores {{sti|mana|{{as|2% '''maximum''' mana}}}} every second."
      ],
      "notes": "* ''Crystal Spire'' distribution is as follows:\n** {{sbc|Six}} in [[Summoner's Rift]]\n*** One beside {{uis|Baron Nashor}} pit\n*** One beside {{uis|Dragon}} pit\n*** One nearby each {{ui|Red Brambleback}}\n*** One nearby each {{ui|Blue Sentinel}}\n** {{sbc|Five}} in [[Twisted Treeline]]\n*** One within {{uis|Vilemaw}} pit\n*** One nearby each {{ui|Golem}}\n*** One nearby each {{ui|Giant Wolf}}\n** {{sbc|Five}} in [[Howling Abyss]]\n*** One in each brush\n*** One in each team's base (below each inhibitor)\n* The ''Crystal Spires'' near {{ui|Baron Nashor}}, {{ui|Dragon}}, {{ui|Vilemaw}}, and the central brush in [[Howling Abyss]] begin the game as neutral and can only be captured after minions spawn (1:30) and onwards.\n** All other spires begin as either allied or enemy (depending on position) but can be captured as soon as the game starts.\n* No additional ''Crystal Spires'' are spawned in [[One for All]] or mirrored matches\n** Every ally ''Skarner'' will receive the bonuses so long as the ''Crystal Spires'' are in allied control.",
      "skillkey": "I",
      "skillid": "i1",
      "effects": []
    },
